statements: SELECT * FROM healthcare_outcomes_data ORDER BY age ASC, outcome DESC LIMIT 10;
SELECT patient_id, patient_name, gender FROM healthcare_outcomes_data WHERE age > 50;
SELECT patient_name, outcome FROM healthcare_outcomes_data WHERE treatment_type = 'Surgery';
SELECT * FROM healthcare_outcomes_data WHERE gender = 'Female' ORDER BY age DESC;
SELECT patient_id, treatment_type FROM healthcare_outcomes_data WHERE outcome LIKE '%Successful%' ORDER BY patient_id;
SELECT * FROM healthcare_outcomes_data WHERE age > 50 ORDER BY patient_name ASC;
SELECT patient_name, gender, outcome FROM healthcare_outcomes_data WHERE treatment_type = 'Medication' ORDER BY patient_id DESC;
SELECT patient_id, patient_name, age, gender FROM healthcare_outcomes_data WHERE gender = 'Female' ORDER BY age DESC;
SELECT * FROM healthcare_outcomes_data WHERE outcome LIKE '%Improved%' AND age BETWEEN 30 AND 50;
SELECT treatment_type, COUNT(*) AS total_count FROM healthcare_outcomes_data GROUP BY treatment_type HAVING COUNT(*) > 1 ORDER BY total_count DESC;
SELECT * FROM PatientData;
SELECT PatientID, Age, Gender, Race, Treatment FROM PatientData;
SELECT Treatment, Outcome, OutcomeScore FROM TreatmentOutcomes;
SELECT PatientID, Treatment, Outcome, OutcomeScore FROM TreatmentOutcomes ORDER BY PatientID DESC;
SELECT PatientID, Age, Gender, Race, Treatment FROM PatientData WHERE Age < 30;
SELECT * FROM PatientData WHERE Age > 30 ORDER BY Gender DESC
SELECT PatientID, Gender, Treatment FROM PatientData WHERE Race = 'Asian' AND Age <= 40 ORDER BY PatientID ASC
SELECT PatientID, Gender, Treatment FROM PatientData WHERE Age BETWEEN 20 AND 50 AND Treatment LIKE '%surgery%'

SELECT PatientID, Treatment, Outcome, OutcomeScore FROM TreatmentOutcomes INNER JOIN PatientData ON TreatmentOutcomes.PatientID = PatientData.PatientID WHERE TreatmentOutcomes.Outcome = 'Successful' ORDER BY OutcomeScore DESC

SELECT PatientData.PatientID, PatientData.Gender, PatientData.Race, TreatmentOutcomes.Outcome, TreatmentOutcomes.OutcomeDate FROM PatientData LEFT JOIN TreatmentOutcomes ON PatientData.PatientID = TreatmentOutcomes.PatientID
SELECT * FROM Patients;
SELECT age, gender, ethnicity FROM Patients;
SELECT treatment_name, dosage, outcome FROM Treatments;
SELECT * FROM Demographics WHERE income > 50000;
SELECT education_level, insurance_type FROM Demographics WHERE demo_id = '1234-abcd';
SELECT * FROM Patients WHERE age > 30 ORDER BY gender DESC;

SELECT Demographics.patient_id, education_level, Patients.gender, Treatments.treatment_name FROM Demographics INNER JOIN Patients ON Demographics.patient_id = Patients.patient_id INNER JOIN Treatments ON Demographics.patient_id = Treatments.patient_id WHERE Treatments.dosage > 50;

SELECT Patients.patient_id, gender, COUNT(DISTINCT Demographics.demo_id) AS num_demographics FROM Patients LEFT JOIN Demographics ON Patients.patient_id = Demographics.patient_id GROUP BY Patients.patient_id, gender ORDER BY num_demographics DESC;
SELECT treatment_name, AVG(dosage) AS avg_dosage, COUNT(patient_id) AS num_patients FROM Treatments GROUP BY treatment_name HAVING COUNT(patient_id) > 1 ORDER BY avg_dosage DESC;

SELECT Patients.age, AVG(Demographics.income) AS avg_income FROM Patients LEFT JOIN Demographics ON Patients.patient_id = Demographics.patient_id GROUP BY Patients.age HAVING Patients.age < 60 ORDER BY Patients.age ASC, avg_income DESC;
SELECT patient_id, age, gender, ethnicity FROM PatientDemographics;
SELECT * FROM TreatmentHistory ORDER BY treatment_date DESC;
SELECT patient_id, treatment_description FROM TreatmentHistory WHERE patient_id = 1;
SELECT outcome_id, outcome_value FROM OutcomeData WHERE outcome_value > 0.5;
SELECT provider_name, specialty FROM HealthcareProviders WHERE location = 'New York';
SELECT * FROM PatientDemographics;
SELECT patient_id, age, gender FROM PatientDemographics WHERE age > 30;
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM TreatmentHistory;
SELECT provider_name, specialty, location FROM HealthcareProviders WHERE specialty = 'Cardiology';
SELECT patient_id, treatment_date, treatment_description FROM TreatmentHistory ORDER BY treatment_date DESC;
SELECT * FROM patients WHERE age > 30
SELECT first_name, last_name FROM patients ORDER BY last_name ASC
SELECT treatment_name, effectiveness FROM treatments WHERE side_effects IS NULL
SELECT * FROM hospitals WHERE rating >= 4.5 ORDER BY location DESC
SELECT doctor_name, specialty, experience_years FROM doctors
SELECT * FROM patients WHERE age > 50 ORDER BY last_name ASC
SELECT first_name, last_name FROM patients WHERE gender='Female' AND age BETWEEN 30 AND 40
SELECT treatment_name, effectiveness, side_effects FROM treatments WHERE effectiveness='High'
SELECT hospital_name, rating FROM hospitals WHERE rating >= 4.0 ORDER BY hospital_name DESC
SELECT doctor_name, specialty, experience_years FROM doctors WHERE specialty='Cardiology'
